      <acqinfo id="aspace_e87adcc2bfe1a81d3d8655901d342b15">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The records were found in the Treasurer's Records and were presumably deposited by William L. McLane when the Corporation went out of existence in 1893.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_2a34293944eb57be2915de0b18f82e96">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_ebb3e327b0956af9e574024fd2838de0">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Yale Gymnasium Corporation Records. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_edb7573d9a0d84823b795c335d25e3f9">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Yale Gymnasium Corporation was formed "to promote and encourage physical exercise among the students and members of the Yale University, to build, equip and manage for their use a gymnasium." To finance its project, subscriptions were solicited from alumni. In conjunction with the University, the Corporation bought land and planned the new building. Included in these papers are the contracts and specifications for the Gymnasium, which was completed in 1892 and formally opened in 1893. In 1893 "the property of the Yale Gymnasium Corporation was conveyed to the President and Fellows of Yale University and the Yale Gymnasium Corporation passed out of existence."</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_9132808d064873ec8c51524b25fd26ae">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Yale Gymnasium Corporation was formed to "to promote and encourage physical exercise among the students and members of Yale University, to build, equip and manage for their use a gymnasium." To finance its project, subscriptions were solicited from alumni. In conjunction with the University, the Corporation bought land and planned a new building which was completed in 1892 and formally opened in 1893.</p>  
      </bioghist>
